The STEEL STAMPING COMPANY, Appellant, v. The N. N. HILL BRASS COMPANY, Appellee. No. 56. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 2, 1936. Rockwell & Bartholow, of New Haven, Conn. (A. J. Hudson, of Cleveland, Ohio, of counsel), for appellant. Howson & Howson,’of New York City (George D. Seymour, of New Haven, Conn., and Hubert Howson, of New York .City, of counsel), for appellee.

• Before L. HAND, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed on opinion below (17 F.Supp. 18).
